oard.com/usaelavee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saela Vee</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>High Priestess of The Kindred</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/27/02 1:22:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.shadowsting.com/images/cat_rocker1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Question for Clerics Supporting Ragefire List</span><hr size=1> Ferhere has posed a question for the Clerics who support the RF list, which I have posted below.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
Ok I have a question about the Ragefire list. Dragon Reborn are strong supporters of the list and it has been funtioning great. Kudos to saela with that said heres my question:<br>
<br>
If for some reson we can not be on to take camp can we remain on the list and the next cleric just passes?<br>
<br>
Reason I ask is that I am currently in the military and we can be deployed to remote locations at any time without having access to EQ or able to play until we return from deployment.<br>
Now if I am the next cleric for camp and am deployed do I have to wait the entirety of the list again after waiting so long(which the same thing could happen again once I reach the top) or can I just inform the moderator that I will not be able to take ragefire camp at this time and allow the next cleric to go until my return?<br>
<br>
Once again GREAT job on list. <br>
 <br>
Ferhere<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uracknarsteelhammer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Racknar Steelhammer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>THogg's Lubba</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/28/02 2:50:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question for Clerics Supporting Ragefire List</span><hr size=1> Ok first let me start by saying RL &gt; EQ.<br>
<br>
Honestly I think it would be up to the cleric that has his/her turn next.  We are all being patient and abiding by a list that makes life alot easier in EQ for us Clerics.  But in doing so we are also potentially waiting 3-4 months for the last part of our epic (#20 on list multiplied by the avg of 6 days on RF = 120 days)<br>
<br>
So to be fair to those on the list when it comes up to their time it should be that Clerics desicion IMO.  And no ill will should be made to said Cleric either whether they say yes or no.  And if that Cleric is unwilling then ask the next and so forth until one agrees.  Personally if I have waited 3-4 months, 5-7 more days wont make or break me.  But thats just me.<br>
<br>
RL happens to us all and to wait so long to only have RL come up and be unable to play sucks if you are at the point of RF and miss out.  But it is also not fair IMO to &quot;make&quot; someone wait another spawn cycle due to someone elses RL responsibilities. <p><p>Racknar Steelhammer<br>58 Templar of Brell <br>Guardians of the Keep <br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=140143>Character Profile</a><br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=257064>Klarisa's Profile</a></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uferhere.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ferhere</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>THogg's Lubba</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/28/02 6:04:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question for Clerics Supporting Ragefire List</span><hr size=1> I know I posted question but I do see both sides. I talked with Saela the other nigth and she had some strong points.<br>
<br>
This is like a double edged sword. If you put yourself in the shoes of the person who got interrupted by real life(which is no ones fault) You would certainly not wish to go to bottom of list and wait another 3-4 months in hopes to reach the top again.<br>
<br>
On the same hand as Saela stated some people plan vacation/time off so they are sure to get the spawn which if they have to wait for you upon return then that messes with there RL which isn't fair to them.<br>
<br>
I kinda agree with Raknar with asking the next cleric below I know I wouldn't mind if someone went in front of me IF they waited out the whole list and had RL screw them over. <br>
They were ahead of me on the list anyways so it would have been 5-7 days if they were present when they hit the top of the list other clerics just got the bonus of getting theirs a little earlier.<br>
<br>
Would like more input on this. Sooner or later we all know this will happen since noone can dictate RL. Better to plan ahead then wait till it's to late. <p><HTML><BODY>
