<br>
Saela  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uluvyen666.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Luvyen666</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Emrok's Daddy</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/29/02 12:41:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question for Clerics Supporting Ragefire List</span><hr size=1> Well here's my 2 cps worth on this....  I have to agree with a swap of positions, as this affects the list in NO way whatsoever.!! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
If Cleric A is in position 2 and Cleric B is in position 5 and the two talk and agree to change positions, the it has NO affect on anyone else on the list as Clerics C thru Z still hold the same position they have on the list. It's really very very uncomplicated and shouldn't require a lot of discussion.  This should of course be used only in situations where RL interferes with a cleric's ability to do the camp, although really it wouldn't matter even if the two clerics just wanted to swap spots (not that this would be likely to happen).<br>
<br>
