Weilder of the Water Sprinkler of Nem Ankh <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/useke2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>seke2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#3333cc>Drinalese</font></span><br>  Posts: 396<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/2/02 6:48:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question for Clerics Supporting Ragefire List</span><hr size=1> so is the consensus that swapping spots in the list is ok, since it only effects the clerics who swap, and not the other clerics on the list? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ualdoran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aldoran</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>THogg's Lubba</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/2/02 6:50:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question for Clerics Supporting Ragefire List</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> so is the consensus that swapping spots in the list is ok, since it only effects the clerics who swap, and not the other clerics on the list<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I'd say something like only the first 3 slots can swap.  That way you don't get someone who's number 15.. paying cleric number 4 10kpp to swap with them.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uluvyen666.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Luvyen666</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Emrok's Daddy</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/2/02 7:23:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question for Clerics Supporting Ragefire List</span><hr size=1> Yes, I would have to fully agree with Aldoran's  comment. Keep the swap to the first 4 on the list so we don't run into this issue. There are some greedy folks out there, and even clerics can be swayed by a nice phat chunk of plat!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Feelsgood <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uferhere.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ferhere</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>THogg's Lubba</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/3/02 2:26:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question for Clerics Supporting Ragefire List</span><hr size=1> I do see the possibility of someone putting a cleric on the list as a place holder. I.E. they never plan to finish epic or it's there alt. Thus swapping from say slot 4 down to slot 25 is no big deal. This would leave open an avenue of abuse from a guild. Altough this would be easily detectable they would have at least pulled it off once or if the list changed hands maybe more.<br>
<br>
Limiting it to the top4 seems to be a suitable alternative since this insures that you went thru the whole list. Also provides roughly 25 days for you to sort out RL issues that would come up. This should be more than suffecient time to hopefully deal with any matters. And should result in the minimum impact to others on the list.<br>
